        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 3 at 12:38PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 1238 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles east of Ruston, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Monroe, Claiborne, West Monroe, Brownsville-Bawcom,
Brownsville-Bawcomville, Richwood, Choudrant, Downsville, Drew,
Fondale, Calhoun, Folksville, Cheniere, Mineral Springs, Caderville,
Eureka, and Lapine.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
